# Development Workflow

## Local Development
- Run `bundle exec jekyll serve` for local development server
- Site builds to `_site/` directory (excluded from git)
- Use `--livereload` flag for automatic browser refresh
- Check [Gemfile](mdc:Gemfile) for dependencies

## GitHub Pages Deployment
- Automatic deployment on push to main branch
- Uses `github-pages` gem for compatibility
- Remote theme fetched from mmistakes/minimal-mistakes
- CNAME file configures custom domain (trujordan.com)

## Configuration Management
- Main config in [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml)
- Navigation in [_data/navigation.yml](mdc:_data/navigation.yml)
- UI text customizations in [_data/ui-text.yml](mdc:_data/ui-text.yml)
- Restart Jekyll server after config changes

## Content Organization
- Blog posts in [_posts/](mdc:_posts/) with date-prefixed filenames
- Static pages in [_pages/](mdc:_pages/)
- Images in [assets/images/](mdc:assets/images/)
- Keep assets organized and use descriptive filenames

## SEO and Performance
- Site configured for SEO with meta tags
- Compressed HTML output enabled
- Analytics disabled (can be enabled in config)
- Sitemap automatically generated